menu "Example Configuration"

    config EXAMPLE_SSP_ENABLED
        bool "Enable Secure Simple Pairing (SSP)"
        default y
        depends on BT_CLASSIC_ENABLED
        help
            This option enables Secure Simple Pairing for Bluetooth Classic connections.
            When enabled, the device will use "Just Works" mode which doesn't require
            a PIN code for pairing. This is typically better for HID devices.

endmenu
